entry.title: Skip static animations on compositor and main
entry.content:
An animation with empty keyframes or with keyframes whose property

values are identical between frames previously ran as a normal

animation. As there is no visual change other than at a phase boundary,

these animations do not need to run on the compositor, and only need

to be scheduled on the main thread at phase boundaries.



This is the first step in optimizing no-op animations. A follow up

patch will short-circuit sampling when the property value is constant.

Another patch will refine the rules for background color compositing

to only consider dynamic properties. Finally, metrics will be added

to track shorthand expansion of CSS properties, which is likely the

most common source of static properties in CSS animations.

entry.title: [iOS][PageInfo] Update security info after full load
entry.content:
If the user opens page info while the page is being loaded, its

certificates might have not loaded yet and so the page is insecure. This

results in page info forever showing that the page is insecure even if

it's not. This CL fixes it by making the view controller request for an

update of the security description if it hasn't been fully loaded.



We also make sure that the security subpage uses the same description as

the root of page info. Previously, because the security subpage was

fetching the security information by itself, the security status could

be different if 1) page info is opened before certificates are loaded

and 2) security subpage is opened after the certificates are loaded.



Fixed: b:327589441, b:328370587

entry.title: [ios] Decouple LegacyBookmarkModel from BookmarkModel
entry.content:
No behavioral changes, pure refactoring.



The general idea is that LegacyBookmarkModel becomes an independent

interface that (currently) simply wraps BookmarkModel, with a more

narrow API. In upcoming patches, another subclass will be introduced

that operates under a shared underlying BookmarkModel instead of

always owning a dedicated instance.



For the handful of cases were the new interface (LegacyBookmarkModel)

isn't sufficient, a side channel is introduced in the factories,

GetDedicatedUnderlyingModelForBrowserState(). This is a subtle API and

one that will, in upcoming patches, require callers to implement

flag-guarding.



Test helpers are trivially forked from components/bookmarks/test, as

the interface is analogous but the code itself cannot be shared.



The patch also includes various test-only fixes such as

verifyBookmarksWithTitle() previously doing something else other than

what the name suggests (namely, match the query against the URL).

entry.content:

encoding. For example, in 720p L3T1_KEY, the average PSNR is improved

entry.content:

view's FocusManager, to ensure that all views can be traversed to using

tab or shift+tab. This is slightly different to arrow key navigation,

behaviour of showing a focus ring and using a simulated enter key

press for the pseudo focused view action. Then, treat PickerItemView

separately as a special case.

entry.title: TabDragDropDelegate: Stop capturing gesture events on drop
entry.content:
TabDragDropDelegate starts capturing gesture events when the user starts

dragging a tab from WebUI tabstrip. Currently it only stops the capture

on its destruction. When the user drops a tab outside WebUI tabstrip,

it keeps the capture until a new Lacros window becomes visible.



This CL changes TabDragDropDelegate so that it stops capturing events

right after the tab is dropped. This should not be a problem

because the release event is the last event that we want to capture.

Original change's description:

> WebGL and PaintCanvasVideoRenderer: Don't discard color space

>

> Behavior change:

>

> When UNPACK_COLORSPACE_CONVERSION_WEBGL is BROWSER_DEFAULT_WEBGL,

> this fixes uploads from HTMLVideoElement and VideoFrame to match the

> WebGL spec and convert to the unpackColorSpace. If it is NONE, then

> preserve the existing Chromium behavior of dropping the color space

> information. This is not what the spec says to do but it is what all

> other browsers do.

>

> This will not change the behavior of using Rec709 video (far and away

> the most common video color space) with an unpackColorSpace of srgb

> (the default and also far and away the most common value). For other

> combinations, this is likely to change behavior.

>

> Code change:

>

> In PaintCanvasVideoRenderer::UpdateLastImage we sometimes use the

> right color space (e.g, when creating the SharedImage) and sometimes

> don't (e.g, when specifying the SkImageInfo for that image), resulting

> in color space information mostly being dropped on the floor.

>

> Fix this by using the same color space information in all of

> PaintCanvasVideoRenderer. Use the existing compatibility helper

> function GetVideoFrameRGBColorSpacePreferringSRGB, but move it into

> VideoFrame for use elsewhere.

>

> In WebGLRenderingContextBase::TexImageHelperMediaVideoFrame, fix the

> places where we would fail to specify the SkColorSpace in an

> SkImageInfo. Replace unpack_color_space_is_srgb with

> needs_rgb_color_conversion, because that is what is being checked.

>

> For HTMLVideoElement and VideoFrame, if

> UNPACK_COLORSPACE_CONVERSION_WEBGL is NONE then preserve the

> existing behavior of dropping the color space information.

entry.title: Apply AlignUpRefCountSizeForApple workaround for both macOS and iOS.

macOS added AlignUpRefCountSizeForMac as a workaround for a crash.

iOS is seeing similar crashes also related to swift as in

crbug/40066367, so apply the workaround to both platforms.



There is some evidence this is related to Swift's implementation of

__StringStorage.create, which will round up the total allocation to a

malloc bucket estimate (16 bytes) and claim any excess capacity as

additional code unit capacity. For large allocations, malloc_size is

consulted and any excess capacity is likewise claimed as additional

code unit capacity. This may be worth further investigation in

crbug/327804972

entry.title: [AriaNotify] Allow queuing notifications in HandleAriaNotification
entry.content:
Previously, whenever an author performed multiple calls to `ariaNotify`,

the notifications produced from this method would be overwritten, only

the last notification would be serialized to `AXNodeData`.



To correct this behavior, this change allows these notifications to be

queued in `HandleAriaNotification` to be serialized all at once later.



Note that the serialization code in `ax_object.cc` still overrides the

notification attributes in `AXNodeData`, this will be updated in later

patches to correctly store a list of attributes instead.

entry.title: Support draining the serialized data from blink::CachedMetadata
entry.content:
Currently blink::CachedMetadata is designed to hold a serialized data.

But this is a bit problematic when we just want to check the existence

of CodeCache or CompileHints in the serialized data. We want check the

existence of them on the background thread before starting a JS parser.

(See https://crrev.com/c/4956763.)



So this CL introduces a new method CachedMetadata::DrainSerializedData()

to drain the serialized data.



Also this CL adds unittests of CachedMetadata.

entry.title: Introduce CompileHintsForStreaming class
entry.content:
This CL refractors the logic which determines whether to produce or

consume the local or crowdsourced compile hint while parsing script

resources with ResourceScriptStreamer in TryStartStreamingTask() into a

new class CompileHintsForStreaming.



This logic is checking the V8CrowdsourcedCompileHintsProducer and

Consumer of the page and the cached metadata from the network service.

Currently this logic is executed on the main thread. But we are planning

to check the cached metadata on the background thread when the

background thread receives the response from the network service to

start the script parsing from the background thread.

V8CrowdsourcedCompileHintsProducer and Consumer of the page are

available only on the main thread. So we will create a

CompileHintsForStreaming::Builder object on the main thread, and call

the Builder::Build() method on the background thread.

(See https://crrev.com/c/4956763)



This CL makes V8CrowdsourcedCompileHintsConsumer::Data as

ThreadSafeRefCounted because it will be dereferenced on the background

thread.



Also this CL deletes copy constructors and assignment operators for

V8LocalCompileHintsConsumer and V8LocalCompileHintsProducer.

entry.title: Video: Change HDR10 MPO promote conditions
entry.content:
Previously, whether the HDR10 MPO should be promoted depended on

whether there's a monitor enabled system HDR feature. If so, it would be

promoted. That said, HDR10 MPO should only be enabled on HDR displays.



However, in the case of multiple monitors, if there are one SDR monitor

and one HDR monitor connected to the system simultaneously, because

we don't know which monitor enabled system HDR, the MPO will always

be enabled, and when the HDR video presented on the SDR monitor, there

will be an abnormal tone-mapping issue because of this.



Since we can't get `HWND` in `DCLayerOverlayProcessor`, to avoid

such issue, the promote condition should be restricted to:



"If any of the connected monitor doesn't support HDR or not having

system HDR enabled, then HDR10 MPO should not be promoted."



Also remove the fullscreen detection logic for HDR10 MPO, since after

we correct `kDisableVideoOverlayIfMoving` feature's behaviour, there

should be no inconsistent tone mapping result anymore.

entry.title: Fix overlapping print page indicator on overlay scrollbars.
entry.content:
In Linux and Windows, when Overlay scrollbars are enabled, the page

indicator that appears next to the scrollbars when scrolling in the

print page preview gets drawn on top of the scrollbars, instead of next

to them.



In MacOS, this issue is avoided by hardcoding a 16px margin between the

edge of the screen and the page indicator. This causes the page

page indicator to be drawn far enough to not overlap with the overlay

thumb, and to not overlap with the expanded scrollbars you see when

mousing over the scrollbars.



This CL expands this margin to also be added when Overlay scrollbars

are enabled in Windows and Linux (both regular and Fluent Overlay

scrollbars).



To reproduce this issue:

1. In Windows, enable overlay scrollbars via

chrome://flags/#fluent-overlay-scrollbars

or chrome://flags/#overlay-scrollbars

2. Go to any web page that would be printed in more than one page and

open the print preview (Ctrl+P).

3. Scroll. The floating square with the page indicator gets drawn on

top of the scrollbar's thumb, instead of floating next to it.



Tested locally in Linux and Windows with both type of scrollbars

(regular and Fluent) in overlay and non-overlay versions and verified

that everything worked as expected.

entry.title: [Tab Group Sync] Add namespace to all saved tab group related classes
entry.content:
This CL adds a namespace `tab_groups` to all saved tab group related

classes. Namespace `tab_groups` is originally used for

chrome/browser/tab_groups which contains definitions about tab groups

such as color and ID. With this change, it also applies to all the code

in //components/saved_tab_groups,

//chrome/browser/ui/tabs/saved_tab_groups,

// chrome/browser/ui/views/bookmarks/saved_tab_groups and related tests.

This will help us isolate and modularize the code further from rest of

chrome.
